{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"cbe93a97-cacf-4af2-9881-014fecdef3ef","content":"For a .NET Web API project, use the `webapi` template:\n\n```bash\ndotnet new webapi -n MyApi\n```\n\n**Authentication options** (via `--auth`):\n\n| Option | Description |\n|---|---|\n| `None` | No authentication (default) |\n| `IndividualB2C` | Azure AD B2C individual accounts |\n| `SingleOrg` | Single-tenant Azure AD |\n| `MultiOrg` | Multi-tenant Azure AD |\n| `Windows` | Windows authentication |\n\n**Example with auth:**\n```bash\ndotnet new webapi --auth SingleOrg --client-id <your-client-id> --tenant-id <your-tenant-id>\n```\n\nFor JWT bearer token auth without Azure AD, start with `None` and add `Microsoft.AspNetCore.Authentication.JwtBearer` manually. Want me to scaffold a project with a specific option?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"c3fc081d-aa0b-437c-8dc2-f28e3ea31e64","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about web API project templates and authentication options. This is a general knowledge question about .NET (likely, given the repository context with dotnet plugins). I can answer this from my knowledge without needing to look at files.","outputTokens":277,"requestId":"0400:2B902C:A43C31:CDFB14:6A012955"},"id":"0f7145af-401f-4310-95f2-0d461621468b","timestamp":"2026-05-11T00:57:00.756Z","parentId":"74ab5c7d-b854-4d36-b563-cc4352645712"}
